node.text:
SURPRISE! For the 16th Anniversary XP-PEN sent me their new 4k screen tablet, it's a gorgeous device and I was shocked the box itself was an art piece on it's own!
I'm incredibly excited to be able to give not one, but THREE of these professional level tablets away with them. 💖 ✨ 
I got to try out the tablet for myself and put some thoughts and info in my stories if you're curious!
They sent me some information on how to enter below:

Giveaway Rules:
1. Follow @cyarine, @xppen_ca and @xppenusa
2. Share this post in your story
3. Comment: Happy 16th Anniversary XP-PEN
Prize: Artist Pro 16TP*3 (One each for Instagram, Twitter and Facebook)
Notes:
1.The winner will have to pay the customs duties themselves if any;
2.Shipping is not available to Africa, the Middle East, South America, India, and some island countries. We’re sorry!

The giveaway will run for a week and winners will be contacted by my account directly. ✨

node.text:
This piece was commissioned by Adobe to celebrate #InternationalYouthDay 2021, with messaging about social media focusing on how it's ruining young people and making them anti social, its easy to forget social media is a powerful tool today's youth is using to connect and cross gaps between people, how much social media actually provides us with a huge community and where we choose to find like minded people that accept us for who we are. Before I had to leave school, despite the bullying and difficult times I faced there, I used the internet and found a true community and sense of belonging.
Every time I receive a message to this day about how someone feels seen by my posts or story I remember that that's what it's all about for me. Connection, kindness, from me and to me, too.

#adobepartner
